WHERE: Hermanus, Western Cape PRICE: R35m WHO: Seeff This 60ha boutique wine farm in the popular Hemel-en-Aarde valley comes with a state-of-the-art manor house with 730m² under roof. The property borders the Onrus River on the northern side and is surrounded by mountains, vineyards, and indigenous fynbos, with about 13ha planted with sauvignon blanc, chardonnay, cabernet sauvignon and shiraz vines. WHERE: Somerset West, Western Cape PRICE: R16.9m WHO: Pam Golding Properties Set in the exclusive enclave of World’s View in Kloof Lane, which offers unsurpassed vistas across False Bay, this large family home is surrounded by mountains, nature reserves, forests and valleys. Recently renovated, the six-bedroom thatched property offers expansive grounds, which include an 81m² rim-flow pool, a landscaped garden and lapa.